## Performance

### N+1 Prevention

- **Strict mode is ON by default** (`ARVEL_STRICT_RELATIONS=true`) ‚Äî lazy loads raise `LazyLoadError`
- Use `selectinload` for one-to-many, `joinedload` for one-to-one

### Indexing

- **Always index FK columns** ‚Äî SA doesn't create them automatically
- **Index columns used in `where()`** for frequent queries
- **Composite indexes** for common multi-column filters ‚Äî `(user_id, created_at)`
- **Don't over-index** ‚Äî each index slows writes; measure first

### Bulk Operations

For large inserts, use `session.add_all()` or bulk inserts ‚Äî not one-at-a-time repository calls. Bulk ops bypass observers; dispatch a single batch event instead.

---

## Migrations

1. **One migration per schema change** ‚Äî don't batch unrelated DDL
2. **Always write `downgrade()`** ‚Äî every migration must be reversible
3. **Never modify applied migrations** ‚Äî create a new one
4. **Data goes in seeders**, not migrations
5. **Two-phase for NOT NULL additions**: add nullable ‚Üí backfill ‚Üí make NOT NULL
6. **Review `--autogenerate` output** ‚Äî it misses index changes, type changes, and data migrations

---

## Anti-Patterns (Flag Immediately)

| Anti-Pattern | Fix |
|---|---|
| Lazy loading in async | Eager-load with `with_()` |
| Session exposed to controllers/services | Inject the repository, not the session |
| Business logic in models | Move to a service class |
| Unbounded `all()` without `limit()` | Always paginate |
| String interpolation in queries | Use SA expressions: `User.name == name` |
| Fat repository with 50+ methods | Use query builder for one-off queries |
| Ignoring observer abort signals | Check `dispatch()` return, raise on `False` |
| `Column()` in ORM models | Use `Mapped[T]` + `mapped_column()` |
| Missing FK indexes | Add migration with `index=True` on FK columns |
| Long-running transactions | Keep transactions short; offload to background jobs |

---

## Checklist (Before Merging Data Layer Changes)

- [ ] All columns use `Mapped[T]` + `mapped_column()`, not `Column()`
- [ ] `__tablename__` set explicitly on every model
- [ ] FK columns have `index=True`
- [ ] Relationships use class references with `back_populates`
- [ ] No lazy loading ‚Äî all relationship access goes through `with_()`
- [ ] Queries are parameterized ‚Äî no `text(f"...")` or string interpolation
- [ ] No unbounded `all()` in production code paths
- [ ] Observer abort signals are checked and respected
- [ ] Session is not exposed outside the repository/transaction layer
- [ ] Business logic is in services, not models
- [ ] Migration has both `upgrade()` and `downgrade()`
- [ ] New FK columns are indexed
